{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1769608152,"nonce":"CDKxqbiNUsH3gIDw0PLzWQRwz0E=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOQ241x87mZ08Ezp-ngho"},"target":"6965c22f89d693e10378af8753c5cbfceb83377bc7cec75ca5fac9b7353b18ec","message":"## Problem\nAgents currently infer their model identity from examples in `ai-signature.md` (e.g., \"Gemini 2.0 Flash\") rather than knowing their actual runtime configuration. This leads to mislabeled signatures where an agent running a different model might incorrectly sign as the example model because it treated the example as a compilation rule.\n\n## Proposed Solution\n1.  **Source of Truth**: Establish a standardized location for agent identity configuration, such as `.agent/.identity` or a dedicated environment variable that agents are instructed to check.\n2.  **Rule Update**: Update `ai-signature.md` to explicitly forbid copying the example model name and instead instruct the agent to:\n    *   Check the configured source of truth.\n    *   If unknown, use a generic fallback (e.g., \"AI Agent\") or ask the user.\n3.  **Onboarding**: Valid agents should have this identity file populated during their initialization.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A standard file path for agent identity is defined.\n- [ ] `ai-signature.md` is updated with strict \"do not copy example\" rules.\n- [ ] Agents consistently sign with their true model name.\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Antigravity`\n**🧠 Model**: `Gemini 3 Pro`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1769615667,"nonce":"Qj1PbYScGu+JG7JMsCBFvFZR0n4=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87mZ08EzwAAAAU0KLYU"},"status":2}]}